page.title: 09STUD FARM MUNDON
page.content:
{Stud Farm}is owned by Mr Binder,he has 700 pigs, 6 cats, 5 dogs,4 horses and 1000 turkeys. There are 6 acres for Mr Binders animals, most of the 700 pigs are piglets,which when they are 25Kg are sent to Surrey to be fattened.The Turkey eggs are sold to different counties like{Italy, France, {Belgium}and{Switzerland,}Mr Binder had also made a contract with{Greece}but Mr Binder had to drop the contract.
The Farm is 250 acres big it is called {Stud Farm}because the owner before bred race horses. The house has 3 X's with iron rods through the other 3 X's. They have the cross ties because it is built on clay. 124 acres are for cereal products.
